<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/8442094-elizabeth-stolar"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1563906826i/8442094._UX100_CR0,16,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/8442094-elizabeth-stolar">Elizabeth Stolar</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I think the answer is very simple: If other beings can&apos;t think or feel, that makes it easy and ok to do whatever you want to them -- kill them, destro<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I think the answer is very simple: If other beings can't think or feel, that makes it easy and ok to do whatever you want to them -- kill them, destroy their homes/habitats, eat them, experiment on them, torture them, enslave them, etc. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
