<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/46915505-linda-grant"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1444414555i/46915505._UX100_CR0,12,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/46915505-linda-grant">Linda Grant</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">The book is primarily about the connections that the author, a naturalist working with the Boston Aquarium, made with several octopuses living there. <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">The book is primarily about the connections that the author, a naturalist working with the Boston Aquarium, made with several octopuses living there. The author learned that these animals can think, solve problems, and have an emotional life as well.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
