    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_4411518416" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4411518416" />
    <a title="Holly R W" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/76100631-holly-r-w"><img alt="Holly R W" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1566252167p2/76100631.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4411518416?book_show_action=true">Jan 03, 2022</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Holly R W" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Holly R W" href="/user/show/76100631-holly-r-w">Holly R W</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/76100631-holly-r-w?shelf=nature-and-animals">nature-and-animals</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/76100631-holly-r-w?shelf=nonfiction">nonfiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/76100631-holly-r-w?shelf=pbt-monthly-tags">pbt-monthly-tags</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4411518416" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13559185918642120997">Before reading the book, I knew next to nothing about octopuses. The author, Sy Montgomery, shares her love for these invertebrates as she educates us, her readers, about them. Montgomery writes about her experiences with the octopuses at the New England Aquarium, where she assisted the staff as a volunteer.<br/><br/> Her major thesis is that octopuses share many qualities with humans, including consciousness. She even goes so far as to say that they have souls. Certainly, Montgomery became extremely atta</span>
  <span id="freeText13559185918642120997" style="display:none">Before reading the book, I knew next to nothing about octopuses. The author, Sy Montgomery, shares her love for these invertebrates as she educates us, her readers, about them. Montgomery writes about her experiences with the octopuses at the New England Aquarium, where she assisted the staff as a volunteer.<br /><br /> Her major thesis is that octopuses share many qualities with humans, including consciousness. She even goes so far as to say that they have souls. Certainly, Montgomery became extremely attached to these creatures. She enjoyed holding hands with them (feeling their tentacles wrap around her arm). She described unique personalities for the octopuses that she got to know.<br /><br /> I have to say that this is beyond my experience. I spent some time watching videos of these octopuses to better understand. However, I am skeptical about some of Montgomery's claims. The older I become, the more I realize that sometimes the best we can do is observe and describe. We are often wrong when we theorize. The octopuses may have awareness and intelligence, but they still remain wild creatures. For example, per Montgomery, they are not social with other octopuses, preferring to be solitary. Sometimes, a female will eat the male octopus that she has mated with.<br /><br /> When my son was growing up and he wanted a pet of every stripe and feather, I told him that if an animal needed a cage to live in our home, then it needed to be free outside in nature. That is what I still believe. Although there will always be aquariums, I have to think that octopuses are better off in the wild. <br /><br />3 stars<br /><br />Here is the author's TED Talk. <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aI4II5AbjPA">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aI4II...</a><br /><br />PBT Note: The book fits the monthly tag for Science.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13559185918642120997" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


